Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.map

Class BaseStringMap<Value>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.map.BaseMap<String,Value>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.map.BaseStringMap<Value>
All Implemented Interfaces:
TryCatchTrait, TryTrait, Broadcaster, Listener, MessageTransceiver, Repeater, RepeaterMixin, Transceiver, Emptiness, Sized, SpaceLimited, Receiver, Transmitter, Nameable, NamedObject, Mixin, Map<String,Value>
Direct Known Subclasses:
StringMap
public abstract class BaseStringMap<Value> extends BaseMap<String,Value> implements RepeaterMixin, TryTrait
A bounded map from string to value. Because KivaKit string maps support type conversion convenience methods, they implement RepeaterMixin and broadcast Problems when conversions fail.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
